00:33:03.283 --> 00:33:07.187 position:30% line:83% align:start
- [Kiwa laughs]
- [eerie moaning]

00:33:08.121 --> 00:33:09.657 position:27% line:83% align:start
What do you think
you're laughing about, huh?

00:33:11.225 --> 00:33:13.661 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

00:33:21.736 --> 00:33:24.639 position:27% line:89% align:start
[motorcycle revs]

00:33:27.709 --> 00:33:29.476 position:13% line:89% align:start
First day back in a while.

00:33:29.511 --> 00:33:30.477 position:16% line:89% align:start
What year are you in now?

00:33:32.479 --> 00:33:33.781 position:10% line:89% align:start
Will you be okay on your own?

00:33:43.525 --> 00:33:44.626 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, wait a sec.

00:33:46.093 --> 00:33:48.061 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry this is partially used,

00:33:48.530 --> 00:33:50.397 position:30% line:83% align:start
but you can use
it to say stuff in class.

00:34:09.717 --> 00:34:11.184 position:5% line:89% align:start
Maybe I'll head into town today.

00:34:13.253 --> 00:34:14.656 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm glad you're back.

00:34:14.689 --> 00:34:16.658 position:30% line:83% align:start
So then, you're
not changing schools?

00:34:18.225 --> 00:34:20.427 position:27% line:83% align:start
Kana had to move
away, so I got scared

00:34:20.460 --> 00:34:22.262 position:24% line:83% align:start
that you were gonna
go off somewhere else too.

00:34:23.430 --> 00:34:26.634 position:27% line:83% align:start
Makio! Fox dance
practice starts today, right?

00:34:26.668 --> 00:34:28.335 position:16% line:89% align:start
Yeah, right after school.

00:34:28.368 --> 00:34:29.737 position:24% line:89% align:start
See? What she said.

00:34:29.771 --> 00:34:31.204 position:5% line:89% align:start
Oh, you should come too, Hiyori.

00:34:31.238 --> 00:34:32.607 position:35% line:83% align:start
You haven't
seen the fox dance yet.

00:34:36.844 --> 00:34:39.514 position:38% line:83% align:start
[laughs]
That's the bon festival dance.

00:34:42.684 --> 00:34:45.620 position:30% line:89% align:start
[birds cawing]

00:34:50.257 --> 00:34:52.860 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

00:35:37.672 --> 00:35:38.740 position:19% line:89% align:start
[woman] Look who it is.

00:35:39.439 --> 00:35:41.576 position:16% line:83% align:start
I was just thinking about
visiting you girls at home.

00:35:41.943 --> 00:35:44.244 position:7% line:89% align:start
So, everything going smoothly?

00:35:44.277 --> 00:35:45.747 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah.

00:35:47.115 --> 00:35:48.248 position:10% line:77% align:start
Let me know if you need help
with your change of
address forms.

00:35:48.281 --> 00:35:50.818 position:19% line:83% align:start
Don't forget, you still
have to do move out paperwork

00:35:50.852 --> 00:35:52.152 position:7% line:89% align:start
for wherever you lived before.

00:35:52.787 --> 00:35:54.221 position:33% line:83% align:start
And how come
you're not in school?

00:35:54.722 --> 00:35:56.524 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Oh, I dropped out.

00:35:56.724 --> 00:35:58.526 position:19% line:89% align:start
Really? I didn't know.

00:35:58.926 --> 00:36:00.460 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yoshi] Hello, hello.

00:36:00.494 --> 00:36:02.262 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, hi Yoshi!

00:36:02.295 --> 00:36:04.666 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'm glad to see
you looking so well, Yui.

00:36:04.699 --> 00:36:06.801 position:35% line:83% align:start
Are Grandma
and Hiyori doing okay?

00:36:07.300 --> 00:36:08.435 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Uh, yeah.

00:36:08.468 --> 00:36:10.705 position:10% line:89% align:start
Oh, that's wonderful to hear.

00:36:10.738 --> 00:36:13.708 position:21% line:83% align:start
I have to get going,
but please remind your grandma

00:36:13.741 --> 00:36:15.475 position:13% line:89% align:start
about the paperwork for me.

00:36:15.510 --> 00:36:16.577 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yoshi] Take it easy.

00:36:20.414 --> 00:36:22.650 position:33% line:83% align:start
Is the house
treating you all right?

00:36:22.684 --> 00:36:23.651 position:19% line:89% align:start
I know it's quite old.

00:36:23.685 --> 00:36:25.419 position:27% line:89% align:start
Yeah, it's great.

00:36:25.452 --> 00:36:27.622 position:21% line:83% align:start
My great-grandfather
used to live there, you know.

00:36:27.655 --> 00:36:29.456 position:10% line:89% align:start
It had quite a bit of damage,

00:36:29.489 --> 00:36:31.993 position:27% line:83% align:start
but Kiwa had some
repairs done here and there,

00:36:32.026 --> 00:36:33.795 position:41% line:83% align:start
and now
she says it's good as new.

00:36:33.828 --> 00:36:34.996 position:33% line:89% align:start
Repairs, huh?

00:36:35.029 --> 00:36:36.496 position:21% line:89% align:start
So, you're all right?

00:36:36.531 --> 00:36:37.999 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm kind of the land lady,

00:36:38.032 --> 00:36:40.500 position:24% line:83% align:start
so please do let me
know if you ever need my help.

00:36:41.002 --> 00:36:43.004 position:13% line:89% align:start
Thank you. We're all good.

00:36:43.037 --> 00:36:44.939 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] It is a little out
of the way though, huh?

00:36:44.972 --> 00:36:46.206 position:19% line:89% align:start
Do you have a bicycle?

00:36:47.307 --> 00:36:49.544 position:27% line:83% align:start
I don't, but
the hills would make that

00:36:49.577 --> 00:36:51.012 position:13% line:89% align:start
kind of a nightmare anyway.

00:36:51.045 --> 00:36:52.714 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] Do
you have your license?

00:36:52.747 --> 00:36:53.581 position:30% line:89% align:start
Motorbike only.

00:36:53.781 --> 00:36:55.248 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, do you really?

00:36:55.883 --> 00:36:56.918 position:30% line:89% align:start
[frame clangs]

00:36:57.852 --> 00:36:59.654 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] This fine
young man is my nephew.

00:36:59.687 --> 00:37:00.822 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh, thanks for this.

00:37:01.022 --> 00:37:02.489 position:33% line:89% align:start
You're good.

00:37:02.523 --> 00:37:04.859 position:24% line:83% align:start
My old man's gone,
and I quit doing deliveries.

00:37:05.760 --> 00:37:08.295 position:21% line:83% align:start
So if you don't mind
it being ancient, it's yours.

00:37:08.529 --> 00:37:10.497 position:5% line:89% align:start
Um, how much do you want for it?

00:37:10.531 --> 00:37:12.399 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'm a little
short right now, but--

00:37:12.432 --> 00:37:14.367 position:24% line:83% align:start
- [man] It's fine.
- No, I insist.

00:37:14.635 --> 00:37:15.837 position:21% line:89% align:start
I insist right back.

00:37:15.870 --> 00:37:17.972 position:27% line:89% align:start
Take it and run.

00:37:18.005 --> 00:37:20.440 position:7% line:77% align:start
[Yui] Um, I'm actually in town
to look for a part-time job,
so when--

00:37:20.474 --> 00:37:21.709 position:24% line:89% align:start
Oh, that's perfect.

00:37:21.743 --> 00:37:24.879 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

00:37:26.748 --> 00:37:28.549 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] <i>Tomoko has been</i>
 <i>advertising for a part-timer</i>

00:37:28.583 --> 00:37:29.917 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>for a while now.</i>

00:37:30.383 --> 00:37:31.519 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you in school?

00:37:31.552 --> 00:37:33.755 position:27% line:83% align:start
- Um, actually--
- She dropped out.

00:37:34.421 --> 00:37:37.058 position:13% line:83% align:start
She came to the evacuation
shelter all by herself,

00:37:37.091 --> 00:37:39.527 position:21% line:83% align:start
but then her grandma
came and picked her up.

00:37:39.560 --> 00:37:40.862 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh, and Hiyori?

00:37:40.895 --> 00:37:43.064 position:10% line:89% align:start
She'll get to stay here too,

00:37:43.097 --> 00:37:45.633 position:27% line:83% align:start
because these two
have the same grandma.

00:37:45.666 --> 00:37:48.569 position:41% line:83% align:start
Wait...
So that means, Yui...

00:37:48.603 --> 00:37:50.538 position:27% line:83% align:start
Which of you and
Hiyori's parents were siblings?

00:37:50.571 --> 00:37:52.305 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:37:52.339 --> 00:37:54.609 position:19% line:83% align:start
Wow, sounds like you've
been through a lot lately.

00:37:54.642 --> 00:37:57.779 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm afraid I can't offer
that much, but if that's okay...

00:37:58.045 --> 00:37:59.279 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:38:00.548 --> 00:38:02.016 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, thanks, I appreciate it.

00:38:04.118 --> 00:38:05.920 position:30% line:83% align:start
- Welcome home.
- [Yui] What's up?

00:38:06.587 --> 00:38:07.855 position:16% line:89% align:start
Where did that come from?

00:38:09.123 --> 00:38:10.992 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Yui] Yoshi's nephew that runs
a noodle shop gave it to me.

00:38:11.559 --> 00:38:12.894 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:38:12.927 --> 00:38:13.861 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yui] And I got a job.

00:38:13.895 --> 00:38:14.929 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh!

00:38:16.363 --> 00:38:18.766 position:27% line:83% align:start
Senda Foods was
looking for some help, so.

00:38:18.800 --> 00:38:20.735 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's wonderful.

00:38:20.768 --> 00:38:21.569 position:33% line:89% align:start
What's that?

00:38:22.837 --> 00:38:26.040 position:24% line:83% align:start
I thought I'd make
Hiyori some pancakes.

00:38:26.073 --> 00:38:27.642 position:27% line:89% align:start
Aren't you sweet.

00:38:27.675 --> 00:38:28.776 position:16% line:89% align:start
I think she'll love that.

00:38:29.877 --> 00:38:34.849 position:16% line:83% align:start
- [music continues]
- [bell tolls]

00:38:43.157 --> 00:38:44.826 position:21% line:83% align:start
My family used to be
the head fishermen here.

00:38:45.793 --> 00:38:48.495 position:21% line:83% align:start
There would always be
a ton of fishing boats nearby,

00:38:48.529 --> 00:38:50.330 position:27% line:83% align:start
and we always had
the other fishermen over.

00:38:54.836 --> 00:38:56.336 position:30% line:89% align:start
Hi, everybody!

00:38:56.604 --> 00:38:58.471 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh, welcome home, Reiko.

00:38:58.506 --> 00:38:59.640 position:30% line:89% align:start
How you doin'?

00:38:59.674 --> 00:39:01.576 position:38% line:83% align:start
That's my
grandpa, and my brother.

00:39:01.909 --> 00:39:03.044 position:30% line:89% align:start
This is Hiyori.

00:39:03.077 --> 00:39:04.579 position:5% line:89% align:start
She's the girl I told you about.

00:39:05.713 --> 00:39:07.815 position:33% line:83% align:start
That's right,
you're the transfer student.

00:39:07.849 --> 00:39:09.416 position:27% line:89% align:start
Nice to meet ya!

00:39:09.449 --> 00:39:10.985 position:27% line:83% align:start
So, this will be
your first fox dance?

00:39:12.520 --> 00:39:13.955 position:7% line:89% align:start
We could put her on the flute.

00:39:13.988 --> 00:39:15.857 position:21% line:89% align:start
The flute. Good idea.

00:39:15.890 --> 00:39:17.024 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'll pull one
and bring it to you.

00:39:17.892 --> 00:39:19.126 position:33% line:89% align:start
I can't wait!

00:39:20.460 --> 00:39:22.530 position:13% line:89% align:start
Makio, we're ready for you.

00:39:22.563 --> 00:39:24.397 position:7% line:89% align:start
Roger that. Let's get started.

00:39:27.068 --> 00:39:28.903 position:16% line:89% align:start
Good afternoon, everyone.

00:39:28.936 --> 00:39:30.805 position:21% line:89% align:start
[all] Good afternoon!

00:39:30.838 --> 00:39:32.874 position:19% line:83% align:start
Thank you all very much
for making the time

00:39:32.907 --> 00:39:33.941 position:27% line:89% align:start
to be here today.

00:39:35.109 --> 00:39:37.712 position:19% line:83% align:start
The summer festival may
have been canceled this year,

00:39:37.745 --> 00:39:40.147 position:16% line:83% align:start
but I remain ever hopeful
that we'll be able to hold

00:39:40.181 --> 00:39:41.749 position:10% line:89% align:start
the autumn festival as usual.

00:39:42.116 --> 00:39:44.118 position:30% line:83% align:start
Many of us are
struggling right now,

00:39:44.151 --> 00:39:45.987 position:5% line:89% align:start
so let's remain mindful of that,

00:39:46.020 --> 00:39:47.855 position:27% line:83% align:start
and use this time
to lift each other up.

00:39:47.889 --> 00:39:49.824 position:27% line:89% align:start
[people clapping]

00:39:49.857 --> 00:39:52.727 position:13% line:83% align:start
That said, let's start with
the musical accompaniment.

00:39:52.960 --> 00:39:54.595 position:24% line:89% align:start
Let's go sit down.

00:39:54.629 --> 00:39:58.532 position:33% line:83% align:start
[traditional
drum and flute music]

00:40:17.585 --> 00:40:21.589 position:13% line:89% align:start
[woman singing in Japanese]

00:40:38.539 --> 00:40:39.907 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hiyori?

00:40:39.941 --> 00:40:41.175 position:24% line:77% align:start
- [woman continues
singing in Japanese]
- Hiyori?

00:40:41.909 --> 00:40:46.446 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

00:40:59.827 --> 00:41:01.963 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Yui] And I gotta change
the address on my license.

00:41:02.596 --> 00:41:04.598 position:13% line:89% align:start
Right, right. That's a lot.

00:41:04.632 --> 00:41:06.667 position:10% line:89% align:start
You can leave all that to me.

00:41:06.701 --> 00:41:08.903 position:21% line:83% align:start
Uh, but I still need
a change of address form

00:41:08.936 --> 00:41:10.705 position:21% line:89% align:start
for my old place too.

00:41:10.738 --> 00:41:12.873 position:35% line:83% align:start
And I don't
think you can do that

00:41:12.907 --> 00:41:14.208 position:5% line:89% align:start
when we're not actually related.

00:41:14.241 --> 00:41:16.010 position:30% line:89% align:start
Never you mind.

00:41:16.043 --> 00:41:18.045 position:35% line:83% align:start
I'll figure
something out, I always do.

00:41:19.981 --> 00:41:21.649 position:30% line:89% align:start
[eerie moaning]

00:41:21.682 --> 00:41:23.751 position:7% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh. Looks like she's home.

00:41:23.784 --> 00:41:24.618 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:41:34.996 --> 00:41:36.130 position:33% line:89% align:start
Welcome home.

00:41:36.163 --> 00:41:38.232 position:5% line:89% align:start
How did school go today, Hiyori?

00:41:52.313 --> 00:41:53.848 position:24% line:89% align:start
What's a fox dance?

00:41:53.881 --> 00:41:57.952 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now that is a very
longstanding community event.

00:41:57.985 --> 00:42:00.988 position:13% line:83% align:start
It's a traditional ceremony
to help drive out evil.

00:42:01.022 --> 00:42:03.090 position:24% line:83% align:start
The local children
dress up like foxes,

00:42:03.124 --> 00:42:05.726 position:16% line:89% align:start
masks and all, and dance.

00:42:05.760 --> 00:42:07.995 position:30% line:83% align:start
Why foxes when
we're so close to the ocean?

00:42:08.029 --> 00:42:09.997 position:27% line:89% align:start
There's a reason.

00:42:10.031 --> 00:42:13.000 position:21% line:83% align:start
And it all began way
back in the days of yore.

00:42:20.975 --> 00:42:23.844 position:33% line:89% align:start
[tense music]

00:42:24.879 --> 00:42:29.050 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] <i>Long, long ago, before</i>
 <i>this beach even had a name,</i>

00:42:29.083 --> 00:42:31.585 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>a monster appeared offshore.</i>

00:42:31.619 --> 00:42:34.188 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>An eight foot sea serpent</i>
 <i>that began to drift</i>

00:42:34.221 --> 00:42:36.257 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>ever closer towards the land.</i>

00:42:37.024 --> 00:42:39.226 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>When people</i>
 <i>approached the shore on foot,</i>

00:42:39.260 --> 00:42:40.795 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>they were sent flying.</i>

00:42:40.828 --> 00:42:42.329 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>When they came by sea,</i>

00:42:42.363 --> 00:42:44.598 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>their boats</i>
 <i>were cracked in two,</i>

00:42:44.632 --> 00:42:47.234 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>and plunged into</i>
 <i>the depths without fail.</i>

00:42:47.268 --> 00:42:50.838 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>And when anyone dared</i>
 <i>look into the monster's eyes,</i>

00:42:50.871 --> 00:42:53.274 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>they saw awful,</i>
 <i>terrifying visions.</i>

00:42:54.375 --> 00:42:56.911 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

00:43:00.915 --> 00:43:04.085 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>The villagers all decided</i>
 <i>they would simply stay away.</i>

00:43:04.118 --> 00:43:06.120 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>And then one day,</i>

00:43:06.153 --> 00:43:09.824 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>a group of foxes paid a visit</i>
 <i>to an old man by the beach,</i>

00:43:09.857 --> 00:43:12.760 position:30% line:77% align:start
 <i>who had always</i>
 <i>been kind enough</i>
 <i>to share his fish with them.</i>

00:43:23.938 --> 00:43:26.974 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>But this time,</i>
 <i>they brought him a gift.</i>

00:43:27.007 --> 00:43:30.044 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>A small knife</i>
 <i>that could cut through evil.</i>

00:43:30.077 --> 00:43:33.147 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>"Use this knife to</i>
 <i>blind the beast," they said.</i>

00:43:35.783 --> 00:43:39.120 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>To support the old man,</i>
 <i>the village banded together.</i>

00:43:39.153 --> 00:43:42.223 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>They played music, and</i>
 <i>danced with ceremonial arrows,</i>

00:43:42.256 --> 00:43:46.060 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>helping weaken</i>
 <i>the evil he was about to face.</i>

00:43:46.093 --> 00:43:49.663 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

00:44:16.023 --> 00:44:18.692 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>Evil that appears</i>
 <i>in the human world</i>

00:44:18.726 --> 00:44:21.095 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>can only be purified</i>
 <i>by humans.</i>

00:44:21.128 --> 00:44:23.430 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>And at the cost</i>
 <i>of one human life,</i>

00:44:23.464 --> 00:44:25.866 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>the monster was</i>
 <i>finally vanquished.</i>

00:44:30.171 --> 00:44:31.839 position:21% line:89% align:start
From that day forth,

00:44:31.872 --> 00:44:35.809 position:13% line:83% align:start
this area has been known to
its residents as Cape Fox Cub.

00:44:35.843 --> 00:44:37.178 position:27% line:89% align:start
So ends the tale.

00:44:37.211 --> 00:44:38.779 position:44% line:89% align:start
Wow.

00:44:38.812 --> 00:44:40.481 position:35% line:83% align:start
So that was
the start of the fox dance?

00:44:40.515 --> 00:44:42.049 position:27% line:89% align:start
It would seem so.

00:44:47.054 --> 00:44:48.289 position:33% line:89% align:start
You ran away?

00:44:48.322 --> 00:44:49.456 position:13% line:89% align:start
What, from dance practice?

00:44:50.991 --> 00:44:51.825 position:30% line:89% align:start
What happened?

00:44:58.966 --> 00:45:01.435 position:30% line:89% align:start
[somber music]

00:45:11.812 --> 00:45:14.248 position:21% line:83% align:start
[man] I can't believe
she lost them both at once.

00:45:14.281 --> 00:45:16.884 position:7% line:83% align:start
[woman] I heard the man who hit
them was asleep at the wheel.

00:45:16.917 --> 00:45:18.319 position:35% line:83% align:start
[man] Who's
gonna take her in now?

00:45:18.352 --> 00:45:20.854 position:13% line:83% align:start
[woman] Apparently she has
relatives in Kitsunezaki.

00:45:20.888 --> 00:45:23.357 position:19% line:83% align:start
[woman 2] Is that wise?
I mean, her voice.

00:45:26.460 --> 00:45:29.163 position:16% line:83% align:start
[woman 3] <i>I heard she was</i>
 <i>the only one who survived.</i>

00:45:29.196 --> 00:45:31.732 position:24% line:83% align:start
[woman 4] <i>She's all</i>
 <i>alone now. Poor thing.</i>

00:45:39.440 --> 00:45:40.808 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hiyori.

00:45:41.175 --> 00:45:42.409 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yoshi] Good afternoon!

00:45:46.280 --> 00:45:47.515 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Yui] A cat?

00:45:47.549 --> 00:45:49.551 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] No farmhouse
is complete without one,

00:45:49.584 --> 00:45:51.785 position:30% line:83% align:start
especially with
no dogs in the area.

00:45:51.819 --> 00:45:54.221 position:30% line:83% align:start
But I couldn't
find the right fit.

00:45:54.255 --> 00:45:56.257 position:33% line:83% align:start
And then this
sweet thing showed up.

00:45:56.290 --> 00:45:58.425 position:19% line:83% align:start
He's soft and friendly,
so I thought you'd get along.

00:45:58.459 --> 00:46:00.361 position:7% line:89% align:start
He does seem sweet, doesn't he?

00:46:01.262 --> 00:46:02.396 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Can we keep him?

00:46:02.429 --> 00:46:04.098 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Can, should, and will.

00:46:04.398 --> 00:46:06.133 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yoshi] That's great!

00:46:06.166 --> 00:46:08.435 position:5% line:83% align:start
And I just know he'll be pleased
to have found a home.

00:46:08.469 --> 00:46:09.937 position:19% line:89% align:start
Let's name him Kofuku.

00:46:10.170 --> 00:46:11.539 position:41% line:89% align:start
Kofuku?

00:46:11.573 --> 00:46:13.941 position:35% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Yes.
It means "tiny luck."

00:46:14.208 --> 00:46:16.511 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've adopted more
than a few cats in my life,

00:46:16.544 --> 00:46:19.113 position:21% line:83% align:start
but I always tend to
give them the same name.

00:46:19.146 --> 00:46:21.081 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's a reminder
that good fortune

00:46:21.115 --> 00:46:22.950 position:10% line:89% align:start
doesn't have to be excessive,

00:46:22.983 --> 00:46:26.186 position:10% line:83% align:start
and we can find small moments
of happiness every day.

00:46:26.588 --> 00:46:27.454 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

00:46:28.389 --> 00:46:30.457 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

00:46:30.491 --> 00:46:31.526 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Reiko] Hello?

00:46:41.302 --> 00:46:42.403 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

00:46:47.041 --> 00:46:49.076 position:19% line:89% align:start
Amazing! A real picnic!

00:46:49.109 --> 00:46:50.978 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, make sure
you eat up, okay?

00:46:51.011 --> 00:46:51.845 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Reiko] Okay!

00:46:57.318 --> 00:46:58.586 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's yummy!

00:46:58.620 --> 00:46:59.853 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Want some tea?

00:47:00.154 --> 00:47:01.989 position:7% line:89% align:start
Huh? Thank you, it smells good.

00:47:07.127 --> 00:47:09.330 position:19% line:89% align:start
Mm-mm. But you weren't.

00:47:09.363 --> 00:47:12.299 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry I was so pushy
about you being there.

00:47:13.434 --> 00:47:16.571 position:24% line:83% align:start
And your family are
all shrine parishioners?

00:47:16.604 --> 00:47:18.906 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Reiko] Oh, yeah.

00:47:18.939 --> 00:47:22.176 position:7% line:77% align:start
They've organized the festivals
for our guardian deity pretty
much forever.

00:47:22.209 --> 00:47:23.578 position:27% line:89% align:start
That's wonderful.

00:47:23.611 --> 00:47:27.081 position:16% line:83% align:start
So then, do you help out
with all the music and dancing?

00:47:27.114 --> 00:47:31.285 position:16% line:77% align:start
Yes! I try to perform in
the summer and autumn festivals
every year.

00:47:31.318 --> 00:47:33.655 position:24% line:83% align:start
Oh, and my grandpa
asked me to teach Hiyori

00:47:33.688 --> 00:47:35.489 position:16% line:89% align:start
the flute part this year,

00:47:35.523 --> 00:47:37.124 position:16% line:89% align:start
but only if she wants to.

00:47:37.157 --> 00:47:40.027 position:13% line:89% align:start
Ah, that sounds so lovely.

00:47:40.060 --> 00:47:41.328 position:13% line:89% align:start
What do you think, Hiyori?

00:47:44.164 --> 00:47:45.132 position:24% line:89% align:start
Yay, that's great!

00:47:48.102 --> 00:47:49.537 position:30% line:89% align:start
And so is this!

00:47:50.371 --> 00:47:52.674 position:27% line:77% align:start
- [Yui chuckles]
- [Reiko] You're so lucky,
Hiyori.

00:47:52.707 --> 00:47:54.942 position:35% line:83% align:start
Do you guys
always eat such good food?

00:47:55.476 --> 00:47:57.044 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Yui] What are you looking at?

00:47:57.077 --> 00:47:59.480 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Oh, just
out at Sodegaura there.

00:48:00.214 --> 00:48:02.550 position:33% line:83% align:start
There used to
be a little Inari shrine

00:48:02.584 --> 00:48:04.184 position:13% line:89% align:start
on that rock by the caves,

00:48:04.218 --> 00:48:06.954 position:30% line:83% align:start
but the tsunami
almost washed it all away.

00:48:07.522 --> 00:48:10.625 position:19% line:83% align:start
Looks like they finally
came to survey the damage.

00:48:10.658 --> 00:48:12.159 position:21% line:89% align:start
Where are the caves?

00:48:12.192 --> 00:48:13.360 position:16% line:89% align:start
You gotta look real close

00:48:13.394 --> 00:48:15.129 position:21% line:83% align:start
if you don't already
know where they are.

00:48:15.663 --> 00:48:17.699 position:27% line:83% align:start
There's the first
one, and the second,

00:48:17.732 --> 00:48:19.233 position:7% line:89% align:start
and the third one's over there.

00:48:19.266 --> 00:48:20.602 position:19% line:89% align:start
The third one is huge.

00:48:21.101 --> 00:48:23.170 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>It can even fit a Sappa boat.</i>

00:48:23.203 --> 00:48:25.372 position:24% line:77% align:start
- [Yui] <i>Which is...</i>
- [Reiko] <i>It's a tiny little</i>
 <i>fishing boat,</i>

00:48:25.673 --> 00:48:27.709 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>and the cave is</i>
 <i>hollow, so on a nice day,</i>

00:48:27.742 --> 00:48:29.943 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>you can go in and</i>
 <i>see how pretty the water is.</i>

00:48:30.144 --> 00:48:31.613 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Cool.

00:48:31.646 --> 00:48:34.682 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] You know, there are
actually four caves down there.

00:48:34.716 --> 00:48:36.049 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Really?

00:48:36.083 --> 00:48:37.552 position:19% line:89% align:start
Where's the fourth one?

00:48:37.585 --> 00:48:41.054 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] It's so deep, you can't
even see it during low tide.

00:48:41.088 --> 00:48:42.222 position:24% line:89% align:start
I never knew that.

00:48:43.290 --> 00:48:46.193 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] <i>The fourth cave is</i>
 <i>the biggest of them all.</i>

00:48:46.561 --> 00:48:49.631 position:24% line:89% align:start
[melancholic music]

00:49:09.183 --> 00:49:13.287 position:19% line:77% align:start
Though now I'm certain
everyone just wanted to forget
it existed.

00:49:14.188 --> 00:49:15.355 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:49:16.524 --> 00:49:19.426 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, anyway, let's dig
into our dessert, shall we?

00:49:19.460 --> 00:49:22.530 position:16% line:83% align:start
And Yui, we'll have some
company tomorrow evening.

00:49:22.564 --> 00:49:25.432 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll need to stock up
on more food than usual.

00:49:25.466 --> 00:49:27.301 position:5% line:89% align:start
Could I trouble you to help out?

00:49:27.334 --> 00:49:29.336 position:30% line:83% align:start
Sure. How many
people are coming?

00:49:29.369 --> 00:49:31.639 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Oh, around
seven or eight, I imagine.

00:49:31.673 --> 00:49:33.340 position:10% line:89% align:start
They're a bit unusual though.

00:49:33.708 --> 00:49:34.609 position:21% line:89% align:start
What does that mean?

00:49:36.210 --> 00:49:37.745 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa gasps] Pasta?

00:49:37.779 --> 00:49:40.715 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yui, can you make
some kind of pasta dish?

00:49:40.748 --> 00:49:41.982 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Like carbonara?

00:49:42.182 --> 00:49:43.718 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] <i>That sounds perfect.</i>

00:49:43.751 --> 00:49:46.521 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>I can't wait to see</i>
 <i>a bit of your cooking magic.</i>

00:50:00.602 --> 00:50:02.670 position:33% line:83% align:start
It looks like
it might rain tomorrow.

00:50:29.429 --> 00:50:31.533 position:27% line:89% align:start
[rain pattering]

00:50:46.380 --> 00:50:47.347 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

00:50:57.424 --> 00:50:58.693 position:16% line:89% align:start
[voice] Morning, Granny.

00:50:59.192 --> 00:51:01.863 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Thank you so
much for coming all this way.

00:51:01.896 --> 00:51:03.430 position:16% line:89% align:start
[voice] Oh, come off it.

00:51:03.463 --> 00:51:06.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
We just came down the river,
it wasn't far at all.

00:51:06.568 --> 00:51:08.670 position:24% line:83% align:start
This is a matter of
the utmost importance,

00:51:08.703 --> 00:51:10.838 position:27% line:83% align:start
so we're ready to
do whatever it takes.

00:51:10.872 --> 00:51:13.307 position:10% line:83% align:start
[voice 3] But I've never gone
diving in the sea before.

00:51:13.741 --> 00:51:16.276 position:19% line:83% align:start
I wonder if it'll feel
the same as the river.

00:51:16.310 --> 00:51:19.581 position:10% line:77% align:start
At the very least, it's bound
to be easier than traveling
on land.

00:51:19.614 --> 00:51:21.281 position:33% line:83% align:start
It's probably
just a little salty.

00:51:21.315 --> 00:51:22.149 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:51:23.751 --> 00:51:25.687 position:7% line:89% align:start
You gave me a fright, my child.

00:51:25.720 --> 00:51:27.454 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

00:51:27.487 --> 00:51:30.390 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

00:51:39.499 --> 00:51:42.436 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Hiyori, meet the Kappa
of the Sarugaishi River.

00:51:42.469 --> 00:51:44.237 position:38% line:83% align:start
- Hello!
- [Kiwa] The Shizukuishi River.

00:51:44.271 --> 00:51:45.840 position:38% line:83% align:start
- Howdy.
- [Kiwa] The Kitakami River.

00:51:45.873 --> 00:51:47.407 position:35% line:83% align:start
- Regards.
- [Kiwa] The Kozuchi River.

00:51:47.441 --> 00:51:49.443 position:44% line:83% align:start
- Hi.
- Toyosawa River here.

00:51:49.476 --> 00:51:50.845 position:7% line:89% align:start
And I'm from the Mabechi River.

00:51:51.613 --> 00:51:52.412 position:33% line:89% align:start
Good morning.

00:51:53.748 --> 00:51:56.551 position:30% line:83% align:start
This little one
is my granddaughter, Hiyori.

00:51:56.584 --> 00:51:59.486 position:21% line:83% align:start
It seems she's unable
to use her voice these days.

00:52:00.320 --> 00:52:03.457 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry to hear that,
but don't worry too much.

00:52:03.490 --> 00:52:05.760 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you just take it easy,
it'll be back in no time.

00:52:23.578 --> 00:52:26.313 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] You see those
three openings down there?

00:52:26.346 --> 00:52:28.783 position:19% line:83% align:start
There's a fourth cavern
just to the left of them.

00:52:28.816 --> 00:52:30.618 position:27% line:83% align:start
But the entrance
is below sea level,

00:52:30.652 --> 00:52:34.154 position:16% line:83% align:start
so could I trouble you to
poke around inside for me?

00:52:34.488 --> 00:52:36.791 position:38% line:83% align:start
I believe
the original cap is long gone,

00:52:36.824 --> 00:52:38.960 position:30% line:83% align:start
and the shrine
was there to replace it,

00:52:38.993 --> 00:52:41.896 position:24% line:83% align:start
but as you can see,
the shrine was destroyed.

00:52:41.929 --> 00:52:43.865 position:10% line:89% align:start
Ah, wiped out by the tsunami.

00:52:43.898 --> 00:52:45.633 position:19% line:89% align:start
I see the problem here.

00:52:45.667 --> 00:52:48.536 position:24% line:83% align:start
You think something
has broken free of its seal.

00:52:48.569 --> 00:52:50.437 position:30% line:77% align:start
- Makes sense.
- All right then,
let's find out.

00:52:50.470 --> 00:52:51.506 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:52:54.676 --> 00:52:55.843 position:10% line:83% align:start
- [Kitakami Kappa] Let's go!
- [Sarugaishi Kappa] Alley-oop!

00:52:56.611 --> 00:52:59.681 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Kappa grunting]

00:53:02.717 --> 00:53:04.719 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

00:53:04.952 --> 00:53:07.287 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's been a busy
morning, hasn't it?

00:53:07.320 --> 00:53:09.924 position:16% line:83% align:start
I may need both of you to
help me prepare dinner today.

00:53:11.726 --> 00:53:12.960 position:21% line:89% align:start
Were you frightened?

00:53:15.730 --> 00:53:18.966 position:16% line:83% align:start
And you know they're not
evil creatures, right, Hiyori?

00:53:22.302 --> 00:53:24.539 position:30% line:83% align:start
No matter what
we look like outside,

00:53:24.572 --> 00:53:25.807 position:19% line:89% align:start
the heart matters most.

00:53:27.709 --> 00:53:29.711 position:7% line:89% align:start
Now, let's go wake your sister.

00:53:31.546 --> 00:53:33.346 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Yui] What exactly
have we been making all day?

00:53:33.380 --> 00:53:35.415 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's almost all cucumbers.

00:53:35.449 --> 00:53:37.484 position:33% line:83% align:start
Well, they're
kappa's favorite food.

00:53:37.518 --> 00:53:39.754 position:35% line:89% align:start
What? Uh...

00:53:42.757 --> 00:53:44.759 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh, you're in on it too?

00:53:44.792 --> 00:53:45.960 position:10% line:89% align:start
So, what's the end game here?

00:53:47.562 --> 00:53:49.831 position:35% line:89% align:start
[bird caws]

00:54:05.079 --> 00:54:07.715 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Thank
you for your help today.

00:54:07.749 --> 00:54:10.417 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll have dinner after
you wash off the saltwater.

00:54:10.450 --> 00:54:13.020 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'm sure being in
the ocean for that long is rough

00:54:13.054 --> 00:54:14.488 position:24% line:89% align:start
even for you guys,

00:54:14.522 --> 00:54:15.590 position:19% line:89% align:start
but I do appreciate it.

00:54:16.456 --> 00:54:18.458 position:21% line:83% align:start
- [Kappa chattering]
- [Yui gasps]

00:54:18.993 --> 00:54:20.795 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

00:54:20.828 --> 00:54:22.395 position:27% line:89% align:start
Ah, there you go.

00:54:22.429 --> 00:54:26.033 position:33% line:83% align:start
Yui, don't be
afraid, but kappa are real.

00:54:26.067 --> 00:54:28.435 position:19% line:83% align:start
They aren't just things
you hear about in stories.

00:54:28.970 --> 00:54:30.972 position:24% line:83% align:start
There was something
I wanted them to check on,

00:54:31.005 --> 00:54:32.673 position:10% line:89% align:start
so I invited them to dinner.

00:54:33.074 --> 00:54:35.009 position:33% line:83% align:start
Keep in mind,
there aren't many humans

00:54:35.042 --> 00:54:36.811 position:16% line:89% align:start
who know kappa are real,

00:54:36.844 --> 00:54:40.882 position:16% line:83% align:start
which means that you and
Hiyori are among a precious few.

00:54:40.915 --> 00:54:43.618 position:21% line:83% align:start
If we're going to be
living together as a family,

00:54:43.651 --> 00:54:46.453 position:10% line:83% align:start
I felt like it would be wrong
of me not to introduce you.

00:54:46.486 --> 00:54:47.955 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:54:47.989 --> 00:54:50.758 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] I do have to ask that you
don't tell anyone about this.

00:54:50.792 --> 00:54:53.426 position:35% line:83% align:start
But what do
you think? Are you angry?

00:54:53.460 --> 00:54:54.394 position:27% line:89% align:start
Do you feel sick?

00:54:55.495 --> 00:54:56.664 position:19% line:89% align:start
You look a little pale.

00:54:59.499 --> 00:55:00.868 position:21% line:89% align:start
How are you, Hiyori?

00:55:00.902 --> 00:55:01.936 position:24% line:89% align:start
You're not scared?

00:55:17.618 --> 00:55:20.320 position:30% line:89% align:start
[calming music]

00:55:21.656 --> 00:55:24.959 position:7% line:83% align:start
As long as you're okay with it,
then I'm okay with it too.

00:55:28.162 --> 00:55:30.531 position:16% line:89% align:start
What a great big sister.

00:55:30.565 --> 00:55:32.967 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're sincere
and very tenacious.

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:35.036 position:10% line:89% align:start
I really love that about you.

00:55:35.069 --> 00:55:36.737 position:19% line:89% align:start
Now then, back to work.

00:55:39.439 --> 00:55:40.141 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Mabechi Kappa]
Thank you for having us.

00:55:40.174 --> 00:55:41.441 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Kitakami Kappa] Coming through.

00:55:41.474 --> 00:55:42.577 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kitakami Kappa]
Sorry for barging in.

00:55:42.610 --> 00:55:43.811 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Toyosawa Kappa]
I wiped my feet.

00:55:43.845 --> 00:55:45.513 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Sarugaishi Kappa]
Forgive our imposition.

00:55:45.546 --> 00:55:46.180 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Kozuchi Kappa]
Uh, what they said.

00:55:47.148 --> 00:55:50.985 position:7% line:89% align:start
Oh, man, this looks delicious!

00:55:51.018 --> 00:55:52.153 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Mabechi Kappa] Yeah, thank you.

00:55:53.921 --> 00:55:56.057 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] So you were able to
enter the fourth cave, right?

00:55:56.090 --> 00:55:57.424 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh, did we ever!

00:55:57.457 --> 00:55:59.627 position:10% line:89% align:start
And man, it's huge in there.

00:55:59.660 --> 00:56:00.995 position:13% line:89% align:start
And we're sorry to report,

00:56:01.028 --> 00:56:02.930 position:30% line:83% align:start
it was just as
you feared, Granny.

00:56:02.964 --> 00:56:05.498 position:10% line:83% align:start
We sensed that something had
definitely been sealed there.

00:56:06.033 --> 00:56:07.735 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Mabechi Kappa]
But it must have run off.

00:56:07.768 --> 00:56:09.436 position:5% line:89% align:start
The cavern was completely empty.

00:56:09.904 --> 00:56:12.506 position:10% line:83% align:start
I think you were right about
the function of the shrine too.

00:56:12.540 --> 00:56:14.542 position:35% line:83% align:start
That's what
broke the seal in the end.

00:56:14.575 --> 00:56:16.544 position:21% line:83% align:start
All we can do is hope
that thing doesn't hurt anyone.

00:56:16.878 --> 00:56:19.680 position:16% line:83% align:start
Call us again if anything
happens. We'll always help.

00:56:19.714 --> 00:56:21.115 position:33% line:83% align:start
Whoa! What do
you call this stuff?

00:56:21.148 --> 00:56:22.583 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's amazing!

00:56:22.950 --> 00:56:24.518 position:30% line:89% align:start
Uh, carbonara.

00:56:24.752 --> 00:56:25.920 position:35% line:89% align:start
It's nice.

00:56:25.953 --> 00:56:27.121 position:16% line:89% align:start
More like kappa-rbonara.

00:56:27.154 --> 00:56:28.656 position:7% line:89% align:start
No, no, go get your own plate!

00:56:28.689 --> 00:56:31.424 position:19% line:83% align:start
My granddaughter, Yui,
made it just for you lot.

00:56:31.759 --> 00:56:33.928 position:10% line:89% align:start
Really? You're a genius, Yui!

00:56:33.961 --> 00:56:36.063 position:10% line:83% align:start
I already told you, get your
own! I'm serious! Give it back!

00:56:36.097 --> 00:56:37.632 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Mabechi Kappa] Hey!
My kappa-rbonara.

00:56:37.665 --> 00:56:39.000 position:38% line:83% align:start
You know,
I've seen these before,

00:56:39.033 --> 00:56:41.102 position:24% line:83% align:start
but I've never had
the pleasure of trying one.

00:56:41.135 --> 00:56:42.703 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Toyosawa Kappa] Go eat
a cucumber or something!

00:56:42.737 --> 00:56:44.538 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kitakami Kappa]
Can say the same to you.

00:56:44.572 --> 00:56:46.874 position:7% line:89% align:start
So who are you really, Granny?

00:56:46.908 --> 00:56:48.876 position:27% line:83% align:start
Are we even sure
that you're human?

00:56:48.910 --> 00:56:51.779 position:7% line:83% align:start
All the creatures from folklore
are what I call enigmas.

00:56:51.812 --> 00:56:53.748 position:5% line:89% align:start
And very rarely there are humans

00:56:53.781 --> 00:56:56.183 position:21% line:83% align:start
who can truly engage
and communicate with them.

00:56:56.217 --> 00:56:58.418 position:5% line:89% align:start
I fall into the latter category.

00:56:58.886 --> 00:57:01.222 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Toyosawa Kappa] Everybody
shut up. I'm gonna sing a song!

00:57:01.255 --> 00:57:02.590 position:10% line:77% align:start
- [Kitakami Kappa] Don't even
think about it.
- [indistinct chattering]

00:57:02.623 --> 00:57:05.126 position:24% line:77% align:start
[Shizukuishi Kappa]
I don't know.
That sounds like fun to me.

00:57:05.893 --> 00:57:08.495 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Toyosawa Kappa] This is a song
from a school by my river.

00:57:08.763 --> 00:57:10.798 position:10% line:89% align:start
I memorized the whole thing.

00:57:10.831 --> 00:57:12.066 position:10% line:77% align:start
- [Mabechi Kappa] Here we go.
- [Toyosawa Kappa] It's got
dogs and cats.

00:57:12.099 --> 00:57:13.968 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's a really cute song.

00:57:14.001 --> 00:57:15.336 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Mabechi Kappa]
Oh, it's cute, huh?

00:57:15.937 --> 00:57:17.238 position:24% line:77% align:start
[Shizukuishi Kappa]
I hope he starts soon.
I can't wait anymore.

00:57:17.271 --> 00:57:18.739 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Toyosawa Kappa] Here I go.

00:57:18.773 --> 00:57:20.508 position:16% line:89% align:start
Wait, I forgot the words.

00:57:20.708 --> 00:57:22.843 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Kappa laughing]

00:57:22.877 --> 00:57:23.711 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Kitakami Kappa] Come on!

00:57:29.884 --> 00:57:32.186 position:41% line:83% align:start
See ya!
Everything was delicious!

00:57:41.729 --> 00:57:43.130 position:21% line:89% align:start
I can't sleep at all.

00:57:48.936 --> 00:57:49.770 position:24% line:89% align:start
Guess she had fun.

00:57:51.105 --> 00:57:54.474 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

00:58:06.587 --> 00:58:07.955 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whooshing]

00:58:08.990 --> 00:58:11.525 position:19% line:89% align:start
[cat meowing, hissing]

00:58:12.994 --> 00:58:14.195 position:33% line:89% align:start
[cat snarls]

00:58:14.996 --> 00:58:16.630 position:35% line:89% align:start
[whooshing]

00:58:17.164 --> 00:58:18.632 position:33% line:89% align:start
[cat snarls]

00:58:19.000 --> 00:58:20.634 position:19% line:83% align:start
- [creature screeching]
- Careful!

00:58:25.106 --> 00:58:26.307 position:30% line:89% align:start
What was that?

00:58:26.340 --> 00:58:27.608 position:38% line:89% align:start
A snake?

00:58:30.611 --> 00:58:31.879 position:35% line:89% align:start
[cat purrs]

00:58:40.888 --> 00:58:42.323 position:16% line:89% align:start
Okay, I'm going to work.

00:58:42.356 --> 00:58:45.593 position:30% line:83% align:start
Oh, I prayed to
a Jizo guardian deity.

00:58:45.826 --> 00:58:47.261 position:38% line:89% align:start
For what?

00:58:47.294 --> 00:58:49.997 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] For you girls to get to
stay here for a long time.

00:58:51.065 --> 00:58:53.701 position:30% line:89% align:start
Oh. Thank you.

00:58:54.835 --> 00:58:55.970 position:21% line:89% align:start
What are you makin'?

00:58:56.003 --> 00:58:57.671 position:24% line:89% align:start
A few bars of soap.

00:58:57.705 --> 00:58:59.306 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Yui] I didn't
know you could do that.

00:58:59.340 --> 00:59:01.876 position:27% line:83% align:start
It's simple. Come
smell all the herbs I put in.

00:59:03.711 --> 00:59:05.679 position:38% line:83% align:start
Oh, wow.
That does smell really good.

00:59:05.713 --> 00:59:07.114 position:10% line:89% align:start
I wanna learn how to do that.

00:59:07.148 --> 00:59:08.182 position:24% line:89% align:start
Rain check though.

00:59:09.050 --> 00:59:10.217 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'll see you later.

00:59:10.251 --> 00:59:12.620 position:10% line:89% align:start
Okay. Have a good day, love.

00:59:12.653 --> 00:59:14.855 position:30% line:89% align:start
[bright music]

00:59:14.889 --> 00:59:16.090 position:13% line:89% align:start
[woman] See you next time.

00:59:16.123 --> 00:59:16.957 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Thanks for coming in.

00:59:18.726 --> 00:59:20.995 position:30% line:83% align:start
Would you mind
making a delivery for me?

00:59:21.028 --> 00:59:23.030 position:21% line:83% align:start
You'd be free to head
straight home when you're done.

00:59:23.064 --> 00:59:24.598 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Sure.

00:59:24.632 --> 00:59:26.000 position:33% line:83% align:start
- Welcome in!
- Oh, hey.

00:59:26.033 --> 00:59:27.068 position:24% line:89% align:start
How are you doing?

00:59:28.102 --> 00:59:29.236 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hello.

00:59:29.270 --> 00:59:30.805 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'm glad I ran into you.

00:59:30.838 --> 00:59:32.706 position:10% line:89% align:start
Those forms I told you about?

00:59:32.740 --> 00:59:34.375 position:38% line:83% align:start
Turns out
they were already done.

00:59:34.408 --> 00:59:36.010 position:30% line:83% align:start
I guess I just
glossed over them.

00:59:36.043 --> 00:59:38.612 position:35% line:89% align:start
What? Okay.

00:59:38.646 --> 00:59:40.347 position:33% line:83% align:start
We're really
understaffed at town hall.

00:59:40.381 --> 00:59:42.016 position:35% line:89% align:start
Sorry, Yui.

00:59:42.049 --> 00:59:43.751 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Yui] No, it's fine.

00:59:43.784 --> 00:59:46.220 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

00:59:58.365 --> 01:00:00.701 position:27% line:89% align:start
[motorbike revs]

01:00:05.139 --> 01:00:06.874 position:27% line:89% align:start
Senda Foods here.

01:00:06.907 --> 01:00:08.109 position:24% line:89% align:start
I have a delivery.

01:00:08.442 --> 01:00:10.277 position:16% line:89% align:start
Great. Thank you so much.

01:00:10.311 --> 01:00:12.780 position:24% line:83% align:start
Could you just put
it right there for me?

01:00:12.813 --> 01:00:13.647 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Sure.

01:00:15.116 --> 01:00:16.717 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

01:00:16.750 --> 01:00:18.252 position:33% line:83% align:start
You guys have
rehearsal today, don't you?

01:00:18.285 --> 01:00:19.320 position:35% line:89% align:start
Goin' well?

01:00:22.256 --> 01:00:23.657 position:35% line:83% align:start
[man] How's
the bike treating you?

01:00:24.225 --> 01:00:25.793 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Oh, it's been great.

01:00:25.826 --> 01:00:27.228 position:33% line:89% align:start
Good to hear.

01:00:27.261 --> 01:00:29.797 position:19% line:83% align:start
Did you come to observe
the fox dance? Or to join it?

01:00:29.830 --> 01:00:31.799 position:27% line:89% align:start
What? I'm just--

01:00:31.832 --> 01:00:33.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's more exciting
the more people we get though.

01:00:34.068 --> 01:00:36.103 position:21% line:89% align:start
That's great, but I--

01:00:36.137 --> 01:00:38.372 position:24% line:83% align:start
Teens' choreography
involves one of these arrows.

01:00:38.405 --> 01:00:39.640 position:44% line:89% align:start
Here.

01:00:39.974 --> 01:00:41.208 position:44% line:89% align:start
Okay.

01:00:41.242 --> 01:00:42.409 position:35% line:89% align:start
I'm not...

01:00:45.946 --> 01:00:47.114 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

01:00:47.848 --> 01:00:48.749 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chuckling]

01:01:05.799 --> 01:01:07.067 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thanks for having me.

01:01:07.101 --> 01:01:08.335 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi's nephew]
Sure. See you next week.

01:01:08.869 --> 01:01:10.905 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi]
Girls, be careful going home.

01:01:10.938 --> 01:01:12.439 position:33% line:83% align:start
The strangest
things keep happening.

01:01:12.473 --> 01:01:14.008 position:41% line:83% align:start
- Huh?
- My poor little dog

01:01:14.041 --> 01:01:16.243 position:13% line:83% align:start
hasn't stopped barking once
since last night.

01:01:16.277 --> 01:01:19.013 position:10% line:83% align:start
One of our neighborhood cats
suddenly disappeared,

01:01:19.046 --> 01:01:22.082 position:24% line:83% align:start
and several people
have said they've seen ghosts.

01:01:22.116 --> 01:01:24.285 position:30% line:83% align:start
You know Murata
from the skewer place?

01:01:24.318 --> 01:01:26.854 position:30% line:83% align:start
He said he saw
his late wife at the front door.

01:01:27.154 --> 01:01:28.255 position:30% line:83% align:start
- [eerie music]
- Darling.

01:01:28.289 --> 01:01:30.257 position:16% line:89% align:start
Let's get going already.

01:01:30.525 --> 01:01:33.827 position:21% line:83% align:start
And a few days later,
he completely disappeared.

01:01:33.861 --> 01:01:36.030 position:33% line:83% align:start
Well, I heard
Komiyama saw his neighbor

01:01:36.063 --> 01:01:39.200 position:16% line:83% align:start
even though she had moved
away long before the earthquake.

01:01:39.233 --> 01:01:41.502 position:27% line:83% align:start
You should think
about moving too, Komiyama.

01:01:41.536 --> 01:01:43.003 position:19% line:89% align:start
You won't miss it here.

01:01:43.037 --> 01:01:44.872 position:7% line:89% align:start
[woman] And it wasn't a dream?

01:01:44.905 --> 01:01:46.807 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Yoshi] He said this
was in broad daylight.

01:01:52.780 --> 01:01:53.981 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Yui] That was kind of freaky.

01:01:55.416 --> 01:01:56.984 position:7% line:77% align:start
I wonder if it has anything to
do with that snake from
last night.

01:01:58.219 --> 01:01:59.753 position:33% line:83% align:start
The kappa did
mention that a seal

01:01:59.787 --> 01:02:01.021 position:7% line:89% align:start
had been lifted from that cave

01:02:01.055 --> 01:02:02.489 position:33% line:83% align:start
and something
might have escaped,

01:02:03.324 --> 01:02:04.458 position:16% line:89% align:start
but they didn't say what.

01:02:04.491 --> 01:02:05.893 position:30% line:89% align:start
[leaves rustle]

01:02:06.994 --> 01:02:07.828 position:33% line:89% align:start
Who's there?

01:02:15.002 --> 01:02:16.136 position:27% line:89% align:start
[leaves rustling]

01:02:16.170 --> 01:02:17.771 position:33% line:83% align:start
- [Yui gasps]
- [whooshing]

01:02:20.074 --> 01:02:23.244 position:21% line:89% align:start
[creature screeches]

01:02:24.546 --> 01:02:26.280 position:30% line:83% align:start
Okay, so there
are two of them now.

01:02:29.250 --> 01:02:31.418 position:21% line:89% align:start
[creature screeches]

01:02:34.822 --> 01:02:37.224 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lion-dogs growling]

01:02:40.961 --> 01:02:41.795 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

01:02:46.267 --> 01:02:47.935 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Yui, Hiyori.

01:02:51.138 --> 01:02:52.373 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Lion-dogs?

01:02:52.406 --> 01:02:54.341 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] We're very
thankful you two came

01:02:54.375 --> 01:02:55.476 position:21% line:89% align:start
all this way to help.

01:02:56.477 --> 01:02:59.246 position:21% line:83% align:start
These lion-dogs guard
the shelter's shrine.

01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:00.914 position:27% line:89% align:start
Oh. They do, huh?

01:03:01.382 --> 01:03:04.251 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ethereal music]

01:03:07.121 --> 01:03:09.323 position:19% line:83% align:start
They've decided they're
going to stay here with us

01:03:09.356 --> 01:03:11.191 position:24% line:89% align:start
for a little while.

01:03:11.225 --> 01:03:14.061 position:21% line:83% align:start
So the pointy snakes,
what are those things?

01:03:16.497 --> 01:03:18.999 position:30% line:83% align:start
Vile creatures
from the days of yore.

01:03:19.433 --> 01:03:21.302 position:27% line:89% align:start
[tense music]

01:03:22.436 --> 01:03:24.572 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] <i>Do you remember</i>
 <i>the sea serpent monster</i>

01:03:24.606 --> 01:03:26.440 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>from the fox dance story?</i>

01:03:26.473 --> 01:03:28.543 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>It was known as Red Eyes.</i>

01:03:28.576 --> 01:03:30.344 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm sure you can guess why.</i>

01:03:32.479 --> 01:03:36.350 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>It used its eyes to make</i>
 <i>people see terrifying visions.</i>

01:03:39.086 --> 01:03:41.556 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>Visions of</i>
 <i>their dear friends dying,</i>

01:03:44.892 --> 01:03:47.461 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>visions of</i>
 <i>long lost loved ones.</i>

01:03:48.462 --> 01:03:51.498 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:03:56.303 --> 01:03:58.640 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>Anguish was made manifest</i>

01:03:58.673 --> 01:04:02.009 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>to torment and drive</i>
 <i>people away from their homes,</i>

01:04:02.042 --> 01:04:03.977 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>allowing Red Eyes to feast on</i>

01:04:04.011 --> 01:04:06.313 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>the cries</i>
 <i>in villager's hearts.</i>

01:04:06.347 --> 01:04:09.584 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>Eventually,</i>
 <i>not a single soul remained.</i>

01:04:15.289 --> 01:04:18.425 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>In these places,</i>
 <i>newly devoid of life,</i>

01:04:18.459 --> 01:04:19.960 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>Red Eyes would make its home</i>

01:04:21.161 --> 01:04:24.532 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>until it was</i>
 <i>blinded and sealed away,</i>

01:04:24.566 --> 01:04:27.301 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>as the fox dance tale goes.</i>

01:04:28.168 --> 01:04:30.938 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:04:35.242 --> 01:04:38.178 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] <i>The fourth cave is</i>
 <i>the biggest of them all.</i>

01:04:38.680 --> 01:04:42.483 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:04:59.333 --> 01:05:03.070 position:5% line:83% align:start
Unfortunately, this story didn't
have a happily ever after.

01:05:03.538 --> 01:05:05.573 position:24% line:83% align:start
What does the part
about crying hearts mean?

01:05:06.206 --> 01:05:07.675 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's just an expression.

01:05:07.709 --> 01:05:09.977 position:7% line:89% align:start
When we suffer, our hearts cry.

01:05:10.010 --> 01:05:12.379 position:19% line:83% align:start
It happens to all of us
at some point or other.

01:05:13.013 --> 01:05:15.249 position:30% line:83% align:start
Before you came
to Kitsunezaki, Hiyori,

01:05:15.282 --> 01:05:17.418 position:33% line:83% align:start
you suffered
a terrible tragedy, right?

01:05:23.725 --> 01:05:25.225 position:27% line:83% align:start
And then you went
through the earthquake

01:05:25.259 --> 01:05:27.428 position:7% line:89% align:start
not too long after you arrived.

01:05:27.461 --> 01:05:30.665 position:24% line:83% align:start
You must have felt
hopeless and very scared.

01:05:30.698 --> 01:05:33.934 position:19% line:83% align:start
What kinds of things go
through your mind now, Hiyori?

01:05:58.459 --> 01:06:01.261 position:24% line:89% align:start
[melancholic music]

01:06:06.801 --> 01:06:10.003 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's very common. Believe me.

01:06:10.037 --> 01:06:12.239 position:35% line:83% align:start
When we go
through something terrible,

01:06:12.272 --> 01:06:14.408 position:10% line:89% align:start
we tend to wonder, "Why me?"

01:06:14.441 --> 01:06:16.109 position:24% line:89% align:start
But remember this.

01:06:16.143 --> 01:06:17.277 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's not your fault, love.

01:06:22.182 --> 01:06:24.084 position:16% line:89% align:start
Right now, the "why me"s

01:06:24.117 --> 01:06:26.119 position:38% line:83% align:start
are being
expressed in different ways.

01:06:26.821 --> 01:06:28.723 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>There's resentment and regret.</i>

01:06:28.756 --> 01:06:30.157 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>"I should have done this,</i>

01:06:30.190 --> 01:06:31.659 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I shouldn't have done that."</i>

01:06:33.227 --> 01:06:35.763 position:19% line:77% align:start
 <i>There's the loneliness</i>
 <i>of losing the people</i>
 <i>closest to you.</i>

01:06:37.264 --> 01:06:41.235 position:24% line:77% align:start
 <i>There's the guilt</i>
 <i>of being a sole survivor</i>
 <i>by random chance.</i>

01:06:41.803 --> 01:06:45.138 position:19% line:83% align:start
Feelings are piling up,
creeping into our daily lives

01:06:45.172 --> 01:06:46.541 position:30% line:89% align:start
more than ever.

01:06:46.574 --> 01:06:49.777 position:10% line:83% align:start
Red Eyes is eating our grief
and building its power.

01:06:53.247 --> 01:06:54.749 position:24% line:89% align:start
But never you mind.

01:06:54.782 --> 01:06:56.016 position:41% line:89% align:start
How so?

01:06:58.318 --> 01:06:59.353 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hey!

01:07:00.487 --> 01:07:01.656 position:38% line:89% align:start
What now?

01:07:07.494 --> 01:07:10.732 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ethereal whooshing]

01:07:15.637 --> 01:07:16.771 position:27% line:89% align:start
What were those?

01:07:16.804 --> 01:07:18.105 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

01:07:18.438 --> 01:07:20.642 position:30% line:83% align:start
Follow me into
town for a bit, would you?

01:07:21.709 --> 01:07:24.512 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

01:07:28.181 --> 01:07:29.751 position:35% line:83% align:start
I know it's
around here somewhere.

01:07:31.218 --> 01:07:33.387 position:16% line:89% align:start
Ah-huh, that must be it.

01:07:45.198 --> 01:07:47.569 position:35% line:83% align:start
Yui, could
you turn the light off?

01:07:52.239 --> 01:07:54.676 position:30% line:83% align:start
I can't express
enough how grateful I am

01:07:54.709 --> 01:07:56.109 position:19% line:89% align:start
that you came this far.

01:07:57.612 --> 01:08:01.549 position:19% line:83% align:start
This is Tanaka, a Jizo
guardian deity from Morioka.

01:08:02.550 --> 01:08:03.551 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yui exhales nervously]

01:08:05.452 --> 01:08:07.722 position:33% line:83% align:start
But I have to
reprimand you for leaving home

01:08:07.755 --> 01:08:09.423 position:21% line:89% align:start
on such short notice.

01:08:09.456 --> 01:08:12.392 position:16% line:83% align:start
Morioka is going to fall
into chaos without you there.

01:08:12.426 --> 01:08:13.595 position:30% line:89% align:start
You know that.

01:08:13.628 --> 01:08:15.462 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Tanaka] I had to come, Granny.

01:08:15.495 --> 01:08:17.832 position:21% line:83% align:start
What if I didn't and
something bad happened to you?

01:08:17.865 --> 01:08:19.667 position:21% line:83% align:start
I couldn't live with
that on my conscience.

01:08:19.901 --> 01:08:21.803 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] I understand
that you were worried,

01:08:22.402 --> 01:08:23.638 position:13% line:89% align:start
but you do stick out a bit.

01:08:23.671 --> 01:08:25.138 position:21% line:89% align:start
Surely you know that.

01:08:25.472 --> 01:08:27.307 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Tanaka] Okay, I get it.

01:08:27.341 --> 01:08:29.409 position:30% line:83% align:start
You don't have
to get so mad at me.

01:08:29.443 --> 01:08:31.278 position:19% line:89% align:start
Oh please, I'm not mad.

01:08:31.311 --> 01:08:32.814 position:19% line:89% align:start
You know I'm grateful.

01:08:32.847 --> 01:08:34.481 position:10% line:89% align:start
Though as long as we're here,

01:08:34.515 --> 01:08:36.884 position:30% line:83% align:start
where have all
the others come from then?

01:08:36.918 --> 01:08:39.252 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Tanaka] There's the Jizo
of sumo fighting spirit,

01:08:39.286 --> 01:08:41.656 position:27% line:83% align:start
Zaimokucho's Jizo
of business success,

01:08:41.689 --> 01:08:43.423 position:33% line:83% align:start
the Jizo from
Nishine and Hanamaki.

01:08:43.791 --> 01:08:46.159 position:16% line:89% align:start
The Jizo from Ichinoseki.

01:08:46.193 --> 01:08:49.229 position:19% line:83% align:start
And the lion-dogs from
the Ikkeijima shrine in Miyagi.

01:08:49.262 --> 01:08:50.464 position:24% line:89% align:start
I think that's it.

01:08:50.497 --> 01:08:52.800 position:38% line:83% align:start
So then,
everyone else is significantly

01:08:52.834 --> 01:08:53.935 position:21% line:89% align:start
smaller than you are.

01:08:53.968 --> 01:08:55.903 position:16% line:89% align:start
That's a relief at least.

01:08:55.937 --> 01:08:58.506 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Tanaka] But Granny,
with the way things are going,

01:08:58.539 --> 01:09:00.407 position:13% line:89% align:start
or look like they're going,

01:09:00.440 --> 01:09:03.176 position:30% line:83% align:start
it won't matter
whether we stand out or not.

01:09:03.210 --> 01:09:05.445 position:27% line:83% align:start
Whenever there's
serious danger brewing,

01:09:05.479 --> 01:09:06.614 position:13% line:89% align:start
we'll all be here to help.

01:09:06.948 --> 01:09:08.348 position:24% line:89% align:start
You need only ask.

01:09:08.616 --> 01:09:09.751 position:41% line:89% align:start
I know.

01:09:09.784 --> 01:09:10.885 position:19% line:89% align:start
And I do appreciate it.

01:09:13.688 --> 01:09:16.557 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

01:09:48.355 --> 01:09:50.424 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:10:00.267 --> 01:10:02.670 position:27% line:83% align:start
I wrote to Kana,
but she still hasn't answered.

01:10:06.306 --> 01:10:07.542 position:35% line:89% align:start
[kid yawns]

01:10:12.680 --> 01:10:13.881 position:35% line:89% align:start
Not at all.

01:10:13.915 --> 01:10:16.584 position:27% line:83% align:start
She said she was
moving to Kanagawa Prefecture,

01:10:17.585 --> 01:10:20.722 position:7% line:83% align:start
and once she had a new address,
she would write me back.

01:10:21.756 --> 01:10:24.692 position:24% line:83% align:start
But I haven't heard
anything from her since.

01:10:25.760 --> 01:10:28.395 position:5% line:89% align:start
And I don't know if I ever will.

01:10:28.863 --> 01:10:30.898 position:30% line:83% align:start
I'm scared that
she doesn't want anything to do

01:10:30.932 --> 01:10:32.834 position:5% line:89% align:start
with Kitsunezaki at all anymore.

01:10:34.635 --> 01:10:36.571 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>My mom thinks</i>
 <i>she only wants to forget about</i>

01:10:36.604 --> 01:10:38.371 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>what happened</i>
 <i>with the earthquake.</i>

01:10:39.607 --> 01:10:43.010 position:30% line:83% align:start
And until then,
she can't move on or whatever.

01:10:43.044 --> 01:10:44.712 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm supposed to understand,

01:10:47.849 --> 01:10:48.983 position:24% line:89% align:start
but I'm still here.

01:10:50.985 --> 01:10:52.920 position:7% line:89% align:start
So is she gonna forget me too?

01:11:12.372 --> 01:11:13.440 position:33% line:89% align:start
You think so?

01:11:24.819 --> 01:11:27.588 position:27% line:89% align:start
[creature hisses]

01:11:28.556 --> 01:11:29.524 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Tomoko] Hi, welcome in.

01:11:29.824 --> 01:11:31.358 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui gasps]

01:11:31.592 --> 01:11:34.829 position:13% line:83% align:start
- [melancholic piano music]
- [Yui breathes heavily]

01:11:40.968 --> 01:11:42.770 position:21% line:89% align:start
[inaudible dialogue]

01:11:54.849 --> 01:11:56.818 position:30% line:89% align:start
[cart rattles]

01:12:00.955 --> 01:12:02.322 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, Yui?

01:12:03.490 --> 01:12:06.694 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yui breathes heavily]

01:12:13.835 --> 01:12:16.971 position:30% line:89% align:start
[gentle music]

01:12:35.656 --> 01:12:37.725 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui sobs]

01:12:45.967 --> 01:12:49.570 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Yui screams, sobs]

01:12:53.975 --> 01:12:56.510 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:13:19.800 --> 01:13:22.169 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:13:46.727 --> 01:13:49.196 position:27% line:89% align:start
[waves crashing]

01:13:55.136 --> 01:13:57.905 position:33% line:89% align:start
[flute plays]

01:14:19.560 --> 01:14:21.162 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa claps]

01:14:22.129 --> 01:14:23.998 position:19% line:89% align:start
You've gotten so good.

01:14:24.031 --> 01:14:25.967 position:33% line:83% align:start
You have some
real talent, young lady.

01:14:27.902 --> 01:14:31.072 position:30% line:89% align:start
[eerie moaning]

01:14:31.105 --> 01:14:32.974 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Oh, welcome home.

01:14:38.679 --> 01:14:39.947 position:21% line:89% align:start
Did something happen?

01:14:51.959 --> 01:14:52.793 position:33% line:89% align:start
He found me.

01:14:53.861 --> 01:14:54.695 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Who did?

01:14:56.998 --> 01:14:58.032 position:41% line:89% align:start
My dad.

01:14:58.632 --> 01:14:59.600 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa gasps]

01:15:02.770 --> 01:15:03.838 position:38% line:89% align:start
I, um...

01:15:04.772 --> 01:15:05.706 position:35% line:89% align:start
I ran away.

01:15:07.775 --> 01:15:09.543 position:30% line:83% align:start
I couldn't live
like that anymore.

01:15:09.877 --> 01:15:11.245 position:21% line:89% align:start
I was about to break.

01:15:12.613 --> 01:15:16.884 position:30% line:83% align:start
So I left, and
then the earthquake hit,

01:15:18.853 --> 01:15:20.154 position:19% line:89% align:start
and I keep wondering...

01:15:20.888 --> 01:15:22.256 position:33% line:83% align:start
why does this
always happen to me?

01:15:26.193 --> 01:15:27.528 position:41% line:89% align:start
It's...

01:15:28.796 --> 01:15:30.097 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's just not fair.

01:15:48.149 --> 01:15:49.183 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Never you mind.

01:15:51.719 --> 01:15:52.753 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't you forget.

01:15:52.787 --> 01:15:56.090 position:16% line:83% align:start
You're the most tenacious
young lady I've ever met.

01:15:56.123 --> 01:15:58.259 position:5% line:89% align:start
And I truly love that about you.

01:16:03.697 --> 01:16:04.331 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Yui breathes shakily]

01:16:10.071 --> 01:16:13.274 position:13% line:83% align:start
Now then, you get weekends
off from work, don't you?

01:16:13.307 --> 01:16:16.677 position:10% line:83% align:start
Next long weekend, why don't
the three of us go visit Tono?

01:16:17.912 --> 01:16:18.946 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

01:16:42.136 --> 01:16:44.105 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ethereal music]

01:16:44.138 --> 01:16:45.339 position:21% line:89% align:start
[creature screeches]

01:16:48.375 --> 01:16:51.312 position:21% line:89% align:start
[creature screeches]

01:16:56.917 --> 01:16:58.052 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Reiko sighs]

01:16:58.085 --> 01:17:00.821 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ethereal music]

01:17:08.796 --> 01:17:11.966 position:21% line:89% align:start
[creature screeches]

01:17:17.104 --> 01:17:18.906 position:27% line:89% align:start
[water splashes]

01:17:25.146 --> 01:17:27.414 position:30% line:89% align:start
[wind blowing]

01:17:29.483 --> 01:17:32.353 position:30% line:89% align:start
[mellow music]

01:17:35.322 --> 01:17:36.757 position:16% line:89% align:start
We can get there in this?

01:17:36.790 --> 01:17:38.225 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Yep, that's right.

01:17:38.826 --> 01:17:40.361 position:13% line:89% align:start
How long is it gonna take?

01:17:40.394 --> 01:17:42.129 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] We're
going against the current,

01:17:42.163 --> 01:17:44.698 position:10% line:89% align:start
so it'll probably take a day.

01:17:44.732 --> 01:17:46.834 position:41% line:83% align:start
- Huh?
- [Kiwa] Fun, right?

01:17:46.867 --> 01:17:48.769 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kozuchi Kappa] Hey,
I'll go as fast as I can.

01:17:48.802 --> 01:17:50.971 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] Well,
don't over exert yourself.

01:17:51.005 --> 01:17:53.040 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yeah, I'll tag in
the Toyosawa Kappa halfway.

01:17:54.275 --> 01:17:57.811 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

01:18:28.008 --> 01:18:29.710 position:38% line:83% align:start
- Granny!
- I missed you!

01:18:30.311 --> 01:18:32.246 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hi! How is everyone?

01:18:32.813 --> 01:18:34.348 position:41% line:83% align:start
- Good.
- How have you been, Granny?

01:18:34.381 --> 01:18:35.749 position:41% line:89% align:start
Oh, me?

01:18:35.783 --> 01:18:37.384 position:13% line:89% align:start
I've been doing swimmingly.

01:18:40.187 --> 01:18:42.156 position:16% line:83% align:start
[female Kappa] Thank you.
You've been such a big help.

01:18:42.189 --> 01:18:45.359 position:16% line:83% align:start
A mayoiga passed through
here a few times before, right?

01:18:45.392 --> 01:18:47.361 position:30% line:83% align:start
If you find one
that suits your fancy,

01:18:47.394 --> 01:18:48.362 position:21% line:89% align:start
you oughta stay put.

01:19:00.374 --> 01:19:02.876 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] You know,
back when I was a little girl,

01:19:02.910 --> 01:19:05.212 position:7% line:89% align:start
this forest was my playground.

01:19:05.246 --> 01:19:08.449 position:21% line:83% align:start
I couldn't have been
much older than Hiyori is now.

01:19:08.482 --> 01:19:11.752 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'd get myself lost,
but I'd always find my way.

01:19:13.521 --> 01:19:17.191 position:10% line:83% align:start
Because this mayoiga is given
to wandering the mountains.

01:19:17.224 --> 01:19:18.158 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Yui] Huh?

01:19:18.192 --> 01:19:21.295 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:19:28.335 --> 01:19:29.436 position:41% line:89% align:start
Ta-da!

01:19:29.470 --> 01:19:31.105 position:24% line:89% align:start
Here we are, girls.

01:19:31.606 --> 01:19:34.475 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:20:10.477 --> 01:20:12.079 position:19% line:89% align:start
Isn't this incredible?

01:20:12.112 --> 01:20:15.082 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's the oldest and
by far the most elegant

01:20:15.115 --> 01:20:17.084 position:21% line:89% align:start
mayoiga in all Japan.

01:20:17.117 --> 01:20:17.985 position:35% line:89% align:start
Take it in.

01:20:18.586 --> 01:20:20.454 position:38% line:83% align:start
- Crazy.
- [Kiwa] I know.

01:20:20.487 --> 01:20:21.989 position:13% line:89% align:start
And we'll be here a while,

01:20:22.022 --> 01:20:23.457 position:16% line:89% align:start
so you'll get to explore.

01:20:25.627 --> 01:20:27.861 position:27% line:89% align:start
[music continues]

01:20:33.901 --> 01:20:36.003 position:10% line:89% align:start
Does that kid live here or...

01:20:36.036 --> 01:20:38.138 position:7% line:89% align:start
Sort of. She's a house spirit.

01:20:38.172 --> 01:20:39.006 position:41% line:89% align:start
Really?

01:20:47.047 --> 01:20:47.881 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

01:20:49.350 --> 01:20:52.219 position:33% line:89% align:start
[grand music]

01:21:00.662 --> 01:21:02.196 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa] Oh.

01:21:02.229 --> 01:21:04.932 position:19% line:83% align:start
The mountain guardians
and the mountain witch came.

01:21:04.965 --> 01:21:07.201 position:35% line:83% align:start
The God of
the Home and the Snow Woman.

01:21:07.234 --> 01:21:09.069 position:10% line:89% align:start
The Boss Spirit from Aomori.

01:21:09.103 --> 01:21:11.338 position:21% line:83% align:start
The Persimmon Spirit
from Miyagi.

01:21:11.372 --> 01:21:13.307 position:7% line:89% align:start
The Fog Spirit from Fukushima.

01:21:13.340 --> 01:21:15.543 position:19% line:83% align:start
and the Drop Pot Spirit
from Yamagata.

01:21:15.577 --> 01:21:17.945 position:38% line:83% align:start
And even
the Liquor Spirit from Akita.

01:21:17.978 --> 01:21:20.481 position:24% line:83% align:start
Goodness gracious,
looks like everyone is here!

01:21:20.515 --> 01:21:22.182 position:30% line:83% align:start
Well, this does
have all the Tohoku

01:21:22.216 --> 01:21:23.984 position:7% line:89% align:start
region enigmas pretty worried.

01:21:24.218 --> 01:21:27.354 position:27% line:83% align:start
This goes beyond
Tohoku. Beyond Japan.

01:21:27.388 --> 01:21:29.890 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's a sense of dread
all over the world,

01:21:30.324 --> 01:21:32.359 position:10% line:89% align:start
and not just for the enigmas.

01:21:32.393 --> 01:21:35.563 position:19% line:77% align:start
Humans are also worried
about areas affected by
the earthquake.

01:21:36.263 --> 01:21:38.332 position:21% line:83% align:start
And they're about to
face even more troubles.

01:21:38.365 --> 01:21:41.001 position:19% line:83% align:start
We believe Red Eyes is
determined to run the humans

01:21:41.034 --> 01:21:42.970 position:24% line:83% align:start
out of Kitsunezaki
no matter what.

01:21:43.237 --> 01:21:45.507 position:16% line:83% align:start
Some of us have discussed
hiding out in the mountains

01:21:45.540 --> 01:21:48.108 position:10% line:83% align:start
near Kitsunezaki for a little
while in case we're needed.

01:21:48.142 --> 01:21:49.544 position:30% line:89% align:start
I wanna go too!

01:21:49.577 --> 01:21:51.245 position:33% line:83% align:start
Sorry, kiddo.
It's too dangerous.

01:21:51.513 --> 01:21:53.581 position:13% line:89% align:start
Are you going? Be careful.

01:21:53.615 --> 01:21:55.650 position:10% line:89% align:start
[enigmas] Be careful, Granny!

01:21:55.683 --> 01:21:58.520 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yes, I promise. I'll be careful.

01:21:58.553 --> 01:22:00.555 position:24% line:83% align:start
And all you enigmas
being there too

01:22:00.588 --> 01:22:03.123 position:33% line:83% align:start
would give me
enormous peace of mind.

01:22:03.157 --> 01:22:06.393 position:13% line:83% align:start
This was the best trip home
I could have asked for.

01:22:06.427 --> 01:22:08.429 position:21% line:89% align:start
[lighthearted music]

01:22:17.739 --> 01:22:20.542 position:30% line:83% align:start
Now then, shall
we sit down to dinner?

01:22:21.275 --> 01:22:23.645 position:30% line:83% align:start
Looks like lamb
and veggies tonight.

01:22:30.451 --> 01:22:31.586 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

01:22:34.722 --> 01:22:36.290 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kiwa chuckles]

01:22:39.359 --> 01:22:41.061 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm curious, Yui.

01:22:41.094 --> 01:22:42.362 position:19% line:89% align:start
What do you want to do?

01:22:42.730 --> 01:22:45.098 position:41% line:83% align:start
- Huh?
- With your future.

01:22:45.132 --> 01:22:47.034 position:19% line:83% align:start
Have you given thought
to what you want to become?

01:22:49.436 --> 01:22:50.638 position:19% line:89% align:start
Can't say that I have.

01:22:51.739 --> 01:22:53.340 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Kiwa] What are
you interested in?

01:22:53.373 --> 01:22:55.108 position:7% line:89% align:start
What do you think would be fun?

01:22:55.142 --> 01:22:56.009 position:30% line:89% align:start
Think about it.

01:22:58.445 --> 01:23:00.481 position:10% line:89% align:start
You don't have to answer now.

01:23:00.515 --> 01:23:03.083 position:21% line:83% align:start
Let yourself get lost
in thought for a while.

01:23:03.751 --> 01:23:07.221 position:19% line:77% align:start
Eventually, you'll come
across something you can't live
without,

01:23:07.689 --> 01:23:09.990 position:27% line:83% align:start
just like we came
across this mayoiga.

01:23:10.592 --> 01:23:13.528 position:24% line:83% align:start
When you do, you'll
know you find your calling.

01:23:16.396 --> 01:23:18.031 position:35% line:89% align:start
